President Biden and Vice President Harris met with a group of civil rights leaders to express their gratitude and discuss the ongoing work that needs to be done. The President spoke about the rise of hate and the need to act against hate-fueled violence. He mentioned a recent incident in Jacksonville, Florida, where five young Black individuals were killed, emphasizing the importance of speaking out against those who want to erase history and ban books in American schools. The Vice President emphasized the need for moral clarity and unity, stating that our diversity is our strength and unity is our power as a nation. The President also addressed the issue of preventing hate and stated that he plans to speak directly to the American people about it. He mentioned that he has spoken with the authorities in Jacksonville and plans to contact the families of the victims, respecting their desire for privacy during this difficult time.